    <entry>
        <title>Choo Choo</title>
        <author>
            <name>Jay Johnson</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://johnson.wtf/choo-choo/"/>
        <id>https://johnson.wtf/choo-choo/</id>
        <media:content url="https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/IMG_8984-2.JPG" medium="image" />

        <updated>2024-04-07T18:28:16-07:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/IMG_8984-2.JPG" alt="" />
                    I recently went to the Mariners' opening night here in Seattle. It was the first time I've been to a baseball game since game 7&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/IMG_8984-2.JPG" class="type:primaryImage" alt="" /></p>
                <figure class="post__image"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/IMG_8960.JPG" alt="A view of T-Mobile Stadium for the Mariners opening game" width="4032" height="3024" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" srcset="https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-xs.JPG 300w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-sm.JPG 480w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-md.JPG 749w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-xl.JPG 1200w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-xxl.JPG 1600w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-xxxl.JPG 2560w"></figure>
<p>I recently went to the Mariners' opening night here in Seattle. It was the first time I've been to a baseball game since game 7 of the 2001 World Series, when the Diamondbacks beat the Yankees. It was a pretty fantastic time, even for someone who doesn't care much for baseball 😜<br>Afterward, we dipped into the bar at a hotel where my friend stayed for a few cocktails. Post-game and post-drinks, I headed back home, taking the opportunity to snag a late-night snap of the Pioneer Square Link Station. It's my favorite station in town; it's truly a stunning train station.</p>
<figure class="post__image"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/IMG_8984-3.JPG" alt="The tunnel wall inside Pioneer Square Station" width="2932" height="2199" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" srcset="https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-xs.JPG 300w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-sm.JPG 480w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-md.JPG 749w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-xl.JPG 1200w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-xxl.JPG 1600w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-xxxl.JPG 2560w"></figure>
            ]]>
        </content>
    </entry>
